						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the wall of Anantaliṅga temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1488 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is fragment and incomplete. It records the construction of a corridar (Pauli, probably to a temple) by Hanumānu, son of Vaijanāth of Kaśyapa gōtra. Hanumānu is described as dingariga a servant.</p>						

						<p>It is dated (Śaka) 1410, Kīlaka corresponding to 1488 A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
